                    <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">Renault Kwid</span> (₹4.98-6.45 L) continues to impress with its SUV-inspired design and surprising 279L boot space, offering maximum style at minimum cost for image-conscious first-time buyers.</p>

                    <div class="div-line"></div>

                    <h3 class="subheading">Quick Buying Advice</h3>

                    <h5 class="subheading">For City Commuters:</h5>
                    <p>Prioritize compact dimensions like the Alto K10 (3,530mm length) or Wagon R for easy parking. AMT/auto transmissions (available in most models) significantly reduce fatigue in stop-go traffic. CNG variants (especially Wagon R's 33.47 km/kg) offer dramatic savings for high-mileage urban drivers.</p>

                    <h5 class="subheading">For Highway Driving:</h5>
                    <p>Opt for more powerful options like the Magnite turbo (100PS) or Swift's refined 1.2L engine. Safety features like the Punch's 5-star rated structure or Amaze's ADAS become crucial at higher speeds. Look for longer wheelbases (Amaze's 2,470mm) for better stability.</p>

                    <div class="div-line"></div>

                    <h3 class="subheading">Price Range Summary</h3>

                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">Under ₹5 lakh:</span> The Alto K10 (₹4.23L) and Renault Kwid (₹4.98L) dominate this segment, offering basic but reliable transportation with excellent fuel efficiency.</p>

                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">₹5-7 lakh:</span> The Wagon R (₹5.78L), Tiago (₹4.99L), and Exter (₹6.20L) provide significant upgrades in space and features while maintaining reasonable running costs.</p>

                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">₹7-9 lakh:</span> This range unlocks premium hatches like the Swift (₹6.49L) and Grand i10 Nios (₹5.98L), along with the safety-focused Punch (₹5.99L).</p>

                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">₹9 lakh+:</span> The Amaze (₹8.09L) brings sedan comfort, while the Magnite turbo (₹6.14L+) and Punch EV (₹9.99L+) offer performance and new-tech appeal.</p>

          
                <div class="div-line"></div>

                <h3 class="subheading">Final Thoughts</h3>
                <p>Choosing your first car depends on your budget, driving needs, and priorities. For city commuting, the Alto K10 or Wagon R offer unbeatable value. If safety is paramount, the Tata Punch or Tiago are excellent choices. Those wanting more features might prefer the Hyundai Grand i10 Nios or Maruti Swift. Consider test driving 2-3 shortlisted models before making your final decision.</p>
